Twitter long has denied that it has engaged in the tactic, called “shadow banning,” to censor users’ political beliefs.
ADEarlier Tuesday, Trump’s social media director, Dan Scavino, accused Facebook of “silencing” him because he was briefly unable to reply to comments posted on his page.
Still, the two incidents drew sharp criticism among conservatives, who have claimed for years that they’re being censored online.
AD"It seems to be if they're conservatives, they're Republicans, they're in a certain group, there's discrimination, there's big discrimination," Trump said.
And I would tell you there is collusion with respect to that, because something has to be going on.”